                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Sharon Springs July 29&#47;5650<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>I received your recent<lb/> communication in due time and<lb/> return you my sincere thanks<lb/> for the courtesy and complaisance<lb/> which you have shown towards me<lb/> in regard to the leave of absence<lb/> which I was obliged to seek.<lb/>  I would state that I have received<lb/> a note from Speaker assuring me that he<lb/> holds the sessions regularly and<lb/> that they are well attended and<lb/> I hope that&#44; as an interimistic<lb/> arrangement&#44; this will prove<lb/> satisfactory.  In regard to the<lb/> lecture I would like to ask whether<lb/> you could not put me down for<lb/> the Sunday subsequent to Dr Adler.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I had in my lecture entirely prepared<lb/> when indisposition forced me to<lb/> interrupt my sessions&#44; but I am now feeling<lb/> so much better&#44; thank God&#44; that<lb/> I shall in all probability return to<lb/> New York by the 10th or 11th of August.<lb/>  I believe that August 17th would not be<lb/> too late a date to close the Summer<lb/> session.  Awaiting your disposition<lb/> on this point&#44; I am&#44; Sir&#44; with best regards<lb/> Very respectfully yours<lb/> Bernard Drachman<lb/> Landon Cottage<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
